---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout-v2.astro";
---

<style>
  .heading-anchor {
    position: relative;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
  }

  .heading-anchor:hover {
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .heading-anchor::after {
    content: "üîó";
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: normal;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .heading-anchor::after {
      right: -1.2rem;
      font-size: 0.8em;
    }
  }
</style>
<Layout title="About">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-6 leading-relaxed md:px-6 md:py-8">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <header class="mb-12 text-center">
      <h1
        class="text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-4 text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl"
      >
        About <span class="font-mono">pwrtools.lol</span>
      </h1>

      <blockquote
        class="border-bunnings-primary-orange bg-bunnings-neutral-light-gray mx-auto mb-6 max-w-3xl rounded-lg border-l-4 p-4 md:p-6"
      >
        <p class="text-left text-sm italic md:text-base">
          What would <span class="font-mono">DEAD_AUTHOR</span> have written, if
          they were offered a $10 Amazon gift card for a product review?
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-right text-sm md:text-base">
          <cite>-No one, ever.</cite>
        </p>
      </blockquote>
    </header>

    <!-- The Concept Section -->
    <section id="concept" class="mb-12">
      <h2
        class="border-bunnings-primary-orange text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-6 border-b-2 pb-2 text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl lg:text-3xl"
      >
        <a href="#concept" class="heading-anchor">The Concept</a>
      </h2>

      <p class="mb-6 text-base md:text-lg">
        The premise for this site came from a simple tweet:
      </p>

      <blockquote
        class="border-bunnings-primary-orange bg-bunnings-neutral-light-gray mb-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 p-4 md:p-6"
      >
        <p class="mb-4 text-base italic md:text-lg">
          I don't think we're ready for the wave of power tool reviews generated
          with the prompts like:
        </p>
        <code class="block text-xs leading-relaxed md:text-sm">
          You are Ernest Hemingway, the famous American author and war veteran.<br
          />
          You have just discovered the Black & Decker CT2000 Hedge Trimmer (skin
          only).<br />
          Your task is to leave a review on homedepot.com highlighting your experience
          with the tool. Your review should include details such as<br />
          - how difficult it was to find a parking spot<br />
          - how impressed you were with the relatively little amount of packaging
          you had to deal with to remove the tool<br />
          - the fact that this tool was made in America<br />
          - the speed in which you were able to trim the numerous hedges that line
          your property<br />
          - the good ergonomics of the machine<br />
          Please write this review in the style that high school students across
          America have come to recognize as "quintessential Hemingway".<br />
          Feel free to compare the concept of masculine identity before and after
          the tool's acquisition.
        </code>
      </blockquote>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-base font-medium md:text-lg">
          A friend replied:
          <br />
          <q class="text-bunnings-secondary-green text-lg font-bold md:text-xl">
            Powerful tool purchased by powerful tool.
          </q>
        </p>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">And that was enough encouragement.</p>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          What started as a humorous concept quickly evolved into a
          sophisticated parody that aims to combine authentic literary voices
          with genuine tool expertise, creating something genuinely entertaining
          (and maybe even surprisingly useful).
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Experiment Section -->
    <section id="experiment" class="mb-12">
      <h2
        class="border-bunnings-primary-orange text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-6 border-b-2 pb-2 text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl lg:text-3xl"
      >
        <a href="#experiment" class="heading-anchor">The Experiment</a>
      </h2>

      <div class="mb-8 space-y-6">
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          While the original joke focused on Hemingway, the planning phase
          (somehow) convinced me to expand the set to 12 authors. The criteria
          was basically:
        </p>

        <ul class="ml-4 list-inside list-disc space-y-2 text-base md:text-lg">
          <li>The author must be dead.</li>
          <li>Their works must be available via Project Gutenberg.</li>
          <li>The set must include Ernest Hemingway and Ayn Rand.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          From there, the idea was to have "The Robot" (Claude, Gemini, etc.),
          select the authors that satisfied the criteria, and also presented the
          widest variety of styles.
        </p>

        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          To capture the styles, I had The Robot ingest multiple books from each
          author (via Project Gutenberg), and summarize their style in a few
          sentences (so that another LLM could use that to seed a review).
        </p>

        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          I later had Claude try and assume the roles of each author (given the
          metadata we had created) and write themselves a social media bio that
          tried to capture the writer's style (while also making them seem like
          the most basic of bitches). Some examples:
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Author Showcase -->
      <div
        class="mb-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3"
      >
        <article
          class="border-bunnings-neutral-medium-gray rounded-lg border bg-white p-4 md:p-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-2 text-lg font-bold">
            Ernest Hemingway
          </h3>
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm italic md:text-base">
            "ü•É Minimalist wordsmith meets maximum power tools üí™ 'The drill
            also rises'"
          </p>
          <p class="text-bunnings-neutral-dark-gray text-sm md:text-base">
            <strong>Style:</strong> Spare, understated prose. "The drill works. It
            cuts clean holes. Good."
          </p>
        </article>

        <article
          class="border-bunnings-neutral-medium-gray rounded-lg border bg-white p-4 md:p-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-2 text-lg font-bold">
            Charles Dickens
          </h3>
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm italic md:text-base">
            "üìñ Victorian novelist crafting epic tool tales üîß 'It was the best
            of drills, it was the worst of drills'"
          </p>
          <p class="text-bunnings-neutral-dark-gray text-sm md:text-base">
            <strong>Style:</strong> Elaborate humanitarian tales with colorful workshop
            characters and social commentary.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article
          class="border-bunnings-neutral-medium-gray rounded-lg border bg-white p-4 md:p-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-2 text-lg font-bold">
            Franz Kafka
          </h3>
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm italic md:text-base">
            "üìö Existential writer turned tool reviewer ‚ö°Ô∏è 'The power drill
            chooses you'"
          </p>
          <p class="text-bunnings-neutral-dark-gray text-sm md:text-base">
            <strong>Style:</strong> Surreal bureaucratic landscapes where drill manuals
            become existential documents.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8 flex justify-center">
        <a
          href="/authors"
          class="bg-bunnings-primary-orange inline-block rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white transition-colors hover:bg-orange-600 md:px-6 md:py-3 md:text-base"
        >
          Explore All Authors ‚Üí
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          The first iteration of this site yielded over 400 reviews (every
          author reviewed every tool); however, the tone of the reviews was
          strangely promotional and unsurprisingly repetitive. They worked as a
          proof-of-concept, but it was clear that some prompt-tuning could yield
          something better.
        </p>

        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          After my partner remarked at the UX of this site was a bit confusing,
          and the viewer would benefit from more "commitment to the bit", I
          decided to follow her advice and redesign the site and the process
          behind the review generation.
        </p>

        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          The new site -- what you're looking at right now -- is meant to be a
          far more coherent experience, predicated upon the viewer's familiarity
          with hardware store websites. (Experience with Bunnings Warehouse is
          nice to have, but really any tool e-tailer will do.)
        </p>

        <div class="text-base md:text-lg">
          <p class="mb-4">
            The review generating process is now more author-dependent:
          </p>
          <ul class="ml-4 list-inside list-disc space-y-2">
            <li>
              Instead of all author's shooting for 200-300 words (for example),
              authors have different expected word counts, appropriate to their
              iconic styles.
            </li>
            <li>
              Now, author's have a "bias" in their tool ratings, so that their
              reviews would be more like a real review left on a website. Not
              all authors assign 5 stars. Kafka, for instance, is inherently
              pessimistic.
            </li>
            <li>
              Human flourishes are now an explicit part of the review-generating
              prompt. In addition to being guided to write reviews that are more
              anecdotal than promotional, the prompt includes touches like
              imaginary interactions with Bunnings staff.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Evolution Story -->
    <section id="evolution" class="mb-12">
      <h2
        class="border-bunnings-primary-orange text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-6 border-b-2 pb-2 text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl lg:text-3xl"
      >
        <a href="#evolution" class="heading-anchor"
          >The Evolution: From Concept to Bunnings</a
        >
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          I've already written about the process that went into the first
          iteration of this site, and you can read about that
          <a
            href="/v1/about#the-process"
            class="text-bunnings-secondary-green underline hover:text-green-700"
            >here</a
          >.
        </p>

        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          In an effort to make this project even more transparent, I tried to
          "self-document" as much of the ideation and code creation as possible
          through saved prompts. I'll continue doing this, so if you ever want
          to see what was fed to The Robot, check out
          <a
            href="https://github.com/stevenpollack/power-tools/tree/main/strategy-docs/archive"
            class="text-bunnings-secondary-green break-all underline hover:text-green-700"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            github://stevenpollack/power-tools/strategy-docs/archive
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Robot Generated Notice -->
    <aside
      id="robot-notice"
      class="border-bunnings-primary-orange bg-bunnings-neutral-light-gray mb-8 space-y-2 rounded-lg border-l-4 p-4 md:p-6"
    >
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
        The rest of this page was generated by The Robot.
      </p>
      <p class="text-bunnings-neutral-dark-gray text-sm md:text-base">
        I don't know why, but it decided to avoid first-person pronouns and opt
        for we/us...
      </p>
      <p class="text-bunnings-neutral-dark-gray text-sm md:text-base">
        To be clear, there is no "we" behind this -- as of 2025-07-15 -- it's
        just a single person (and a Robot assistant).
      </p>
    </aside>

    <!-- Current Experience -->
    <section id="current-experience" class="mb-12">
      <h2
        class="border-bunnings-primary-orange text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-6 border-b-2 pb-2 text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl lg:text-3xl"
      >
        <a href="#current-experience" class="heading-anchor"
          >Robot-generated Copy</a
        >
      </h2>

      <p class="mb-8 text-base md:text-lg">
        Today's site combines <strong
          >professional Bunnings-inspired design</strong
        >
        with <strong>genuinely entertaining literary content</strong>. The
        experience feels like browsing a real hardware store catalog, if that
        catalog happened to be written by history's greatest authors.
      </p>

      <div class="mb-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-6">
        <article
          class="border-bunnings-neutral-medium-gray rounded-lg border bg-white p-4 md:p-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-3 text-lg font-bold">
            Smart Discovery
          </h3>
          <p class="text-bunnings-neutral-dark-gray text-sm md:text-base">
            Filter by author voice, tool category, or search specific tools.
            Advanced masonry layout with intelligent sorting ensures you always
            find something entertaining.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article
          class="border-bunnings-neutral-medium-gray rounded-lg border bg-white p-4 md:p-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-3 text-lg font-bold">
            Authentic Reviews
          </h3>
          <p class="text-bunnings-neutral-dark-gray text-sm md:text-base">
            Each review includes realistic project contexts, Bunnings shopping
            experiences, and honest tool performance assessments‚Äîjust filtered
            through literary genius.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article
          class="border-bunnings-neutral-medium-gray rounded-lg border bg-white p-4 md:p-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-3 text-lg font-bold">
            Mobile Optimized
          </h3>
          <p class="text-bunnings-neutral-dark-gray text-sm md:text-base">
            Lightning-fast page loads, responsive design, and touch-friendly
            interactions. 40% performance improvement over v1 with server-side
            rendering.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article
          class="border-bunnings-neutral-medium-gray rounded-lg border bg-white p-4 md:p-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-3 text-lg font-bold">
            Professional Polish
          </h3>
          <p class="text-bunnings-neutral-dark-gray text-sm md:text-base">
            Bunnings-accurate color schemes, typography, and UI patterns create
            an authentic hardware store aesthetic without losing the
            entertainment value.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center">
        <h3
          class="text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-4 text-lg font-bold md:text-xl"
        >
          Ready to explore?
        </h3>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:justify-center sm:gap-4">
          <a
            href="/"
            class="bg-bunnings-primary-orange inline-block rounded-lg px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white transition-colors hover:bg-orange-600 md:px-6 md:py-3 md:text-base"
          >
            Browse Reviews
          </a>
          <a
            href="/authors"
            class="border-bunnings-secondary-green text-bunnings-secondary-green hover:bg-bunnings-neutral-light-gray inline-block rounded-lg border-2 bg-white px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium transition-colors md:px-6 md:py-3 md:text-base"
          >
            Meet the Authors
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Behind the Scenes -->
    <section id="behind-the-scenes" class="mb-12">
      <h2
        class="border-bunnings-primary-orange text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-6 border-b-2 pb-2 text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl lg:text-3xl"
      >
        <a href="#behind-the-scenes" class="heading-anchor">Behind the Scenes</a
        >
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          This project represents a unique intersection of literary
          appreciation, technical craftsmanship, and Australian hardware
          culture. Built with
          <strong>Astro v5</strong>, <strong>React</strong>, and <strong
            >Tailwind CSS</strong
          >, the site demonstrates that parody can be both entertaining and
          technically excellent.
        </p>

        <p class="text-base md:text-lg">
          The code is open source, the process is documented, and the absurdity
          is intentional. We believe in the joy of well-executed ideas, no
          matter how ridiculous the premise.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Contact & Links -->
      <div class="bg-bunnings-neutral-light-gray mt-8 rounded-lg p-4 md:p-6">
        <h3
          class="text-bunnings-secondary-green mb-4 text-lg font-bold md:text-xl"
        >
          Get Involved
        </h3>
        <p class="mb-6 text-base md:text-lg">
          Missing your favorite power tool or author? Found a bug? Want to
          contribute? We'd love to hear from you:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/stevenpollack/power-tools"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-bunnings-secondary-green flex items-center gap-3 transition-colors hover:text-green-700"
          >
            <span class="text-lg md:text-xl">üîß</span>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium md:text-base"
              >View the code on GitHub</span
            >
          </a>

          <a
            href="https://github.com/stevenpollack/power-tools/issues/new/choose"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-bunnings-secondary-green flex items-center gap-3 transition-colors hover:text-green-700"
          >
            <span class="text-lg md:text-xl">üêõ</span>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium md:text-base"
              >Report an issue or request a feature</span
            >
          </a>

          <a
            href="mailto:steep.ship0287@fastmail.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-bunnings-secondary-green flex items-center gap-3 transition-colors hover:text-green-700"
          >
            <span class="text-lg md:text-xl">‚úâÔ∏è</span>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium md:text-base"
              >Send us an email</span
            >
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
